org.opentcs.util

Class UniqueStringGenerator<S>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentcs.util.UniqueStringGenerator<S>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - The type of the selectors/keys to be used for mapping to name patterns.

    public class UniqueStringGenerator<S>
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides a way to acquire unique strings.

                                java.lang.String prefix,
                                java.lang.String suffixPattern)

        Parameters:

        prefix - The prefix of names to be used for the given selector.

      • addString

        public void addString(java.lang.String newString)
        Adds a String to those known by this generator. As a result, this generator will never return a String that is equal to the given one.
        Parameters:
        newString - The string to be added.

      • removeString

        public void removeString(java.lang.String rmString)
        Makes this generator forget a known String. As a result, this generator might return a String that is equal to the given one in the future.
        Parameters:
        rmString - The string to be forgotten.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Removes all known Strings.

      • getUniqueString

        public java.lang.String getUniqueString(S selector)
        Returns a string that is unique among all strings registered with this generator.
        Parameters:
        selector - A selector for the name pattern to be used.
        Returns:
        A string that is unique among all strings registered with this generator.

      • getUniqueString

        public java.lang.String getUniqueString(java.lang.String prefix,
                                        java.lang.String suffixPattern)
        Returns a String that is unique among all known Strings in this generator. The returned String will consist of the given prefix followed by an integer formatted according to the given pattern. The pattern has to be of the form understood by java.text.DecimalFormat.
        Parameters:
        prefix - The prefix of the String to be generated.
        suffixPattern - A pattern describing the suffix of the generated String. Must be of the form understood by java.text.DecimalFormat.
        Returns:
        A String that is unique among all known Strings.
